sequenceDiagram
    participant Client as Client
    participant AGW as Agent Gateway
    participant IdP as Downstream IdP (OIDC)
    participant STS as Token Exchange Server (STS)
    participant UI as Solo Enterprise UI
    participant OAuth as Upstream OAuth Provider
    participant API as Upstream API

    Note over Client,API: Phase 1 — Downstream OIDC Authentication
    Client->>AGW: Request resource
    AGW-->>Client: 302 Redirect to IdP
    Client->>IdP: Authorization Code Flow
    IdP-->>Client: Authorization code
    Client->>AGW: Callback with code
    AGW->>IdP: Exchange code for tokens
    IdP-->>AGW: Bearer JWT + id_token
    Note over Client: Client authenticated with downstream JWT

    Note over Client,API: Phase 2 — Upstream Credential Gathering (Elicitation)
    Client->>AGW: Request upstream API<br/>(with downstream JWT)
    AGW->>STS: Request upstream token
    STS-->>AGW: Elicitation URL (PENDING)
    AGW->>Client: Return elicitation URL
    Client->>UI: Open elicitation URL
    UI->>OAuth: Redirect to upstream OAuth provider
    OAuth-->>UI: Authorization code
    UI->>STS: Complete elicitation with code
    STS->>STS: Store upstream token<br/>(status: COMPLETED)

    Note over Client,API: Phase 3 — Authenticated Request with Upstream Token
    Client->>AGW: Retry request<br/>(with downstream JWT)
    AGW->>STS: Fetch stored upstream token
    STS-->>AGW: Upstream OAuth token
    AGW->>API: Forward request +<br/>inject upstream token
    API-->>AGW: Response
    AGW-->>Client: Response
    Note over Client,IdP: Two OAuth flows:<br/>1. OIDC (downstream) — authenticates user<br/>2. Elicitation (upstream) — gathers API credentials
